decision_conditions:
Condition : 17 - Prior to the commencement of development, a Construction and Environmental Management Plan (CEMP) shall be submitted to and be approved in writing by the local planning authority. The CEMP shall include measures to mitigate the construction effects as part of a coordinated and collaborative approach with surrounding developments, and shall include specific details for:  
a)	the relevant licences from adjoining landowners that will enable access for the chosen construction method;  
b)	the control of construction noise and vibration during hours of noisy activities;  
c)	a construction waste and material management, transportation and disposal strategy, including construction delivery booking and construction vehicle holding arrangements, and targets and arrangements for maximising the use of the river for material removal and material delivery where feasible;  
d)	a low emission strategy for construction traffic and machinery;  
e)	piling or other penetrative methods of foundation design in relation to risks to underlying groundwater;  
f)	measures to protect controlled waters from construction processes and contamination;  
g)	measures to minimise cross contamination on site;  
h)	measures to deal with unexpected contamination on site;  
i)	details of storage of construction materials and machinery and siting of skips during demolition and construction;  
j)	details of security of the construction site in relation to adjacent sites;  
k)	details of coordination of construction activities with neighbouring development sites;  
l)	details of measures to prevent dust and pollution throughout construction period;  
m)	an Invasive Non-Native Species (INNS) Plan providing details of the measures to be taken to remove and eradicate INNS in line with best practice for London (including but not limited to butterfly-bush (Buddleia davidii) and Green alkanet (Pentaglottis sempervirens), both on the London Invasive Species Initiative (LISI) list) and should includ
